> [!IMPORTANT]
> The existing `inspections.py` endpoint file targets tables called `checklists` and `checklist_questions` which appear to be old/different tables. The new endpoints will target `templates`, `checklist_items`, `inspections`, and `inspection_answers` only. The old file will be **kept intact** â€” we will register the new router alongside it.

> [!WARNING]
> **The `Assignchecklist.tsx` screen is being repurposed.** Currently it shows an inline checklist execution UI (Yes/No/NA buttons). The flow you specified says:  
> - `Assignchecklist` â†’ create an **inspection** linked to a template  
> - A separate **Checklist Execution page** â†’ save answers  
> We will make `Assignchecklist` a proper "assign + create inspection" screen, and `ChecklistScreen.tsx` will be the execution (answer-saving) screen.

> [!NOTE]
